 Mexico has registered its worst week yet of the pandemic, with a record number of infections from the new coronavirus and more than 7,000 COVID-19 deaths, government data showed on Saturday.
There were 20,523 new coronavirus cases and 1,219 more fatalities on Saturday, pushing total confirmed infections to 1,630,258 and deaths to 140,241, the Health Ministry said.
For the week ending Saturday, Mexico recorded more than 7,000 deaths for the first time, while posting over 106,200 new cases, reports Reuters.
